5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1198, L.D. 1787, “An Act to Strengthen
10 the Maine Clean Election Act”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Increase Seed Money Contribution Limits for Gubernatorial Candidates
13 Under the Maine Clean Election Act'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
15 following:
16 'Sec. 1. 21-A MRSA §1122, sub-§9, as amended by PL 2007, c. 571, §10, is further
17 amended to read:
18 9. Seed money contribution. "Seed money contribution" means, for a gubernatorial
19 participating candidate, a contribution of no more than $250 per individual made to the
20 participating candidate, including the candidate or the candidate's spouse or domestic
21 partner. For any other participating candidate, "seed money contribution" means a
22 contribution of no more than $100 per individual made to a the participating candidate,
23 including the candidate or the candidate's spouse or domestic partner.'
24 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
25 number to read consecutively.
26 SUMMARY
2277 This amendment replaces the bill and changes the title. The amendment increases the
2288 contribution limits for gubernatorial seed money contributions to $250 per individual.
2299 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
